Leetcode-234.-Palindrome-Linked-List
Description
Given the head of a singly linked list, return true if it is a palindrome or false otherwise.

Solution
In the problem we have been a linked list , and we have to check whether the list is palindromic or not .

A palindrome is a set of numbers that reads the same forwards and backward.

Example 1:

Input: head = [1,2,2,1]

Output: true

Example 2:

Input: head = [1,2]

Output: false

Since this is a linked list , finding palindrome will be slightly difficult hence , we can append all the characters of this linked list to an array . The operations performed in an array will make it easier for us to check whether the given list is a palindrome or not .

Algorithm
Create an empty array named nums.
Use while loop until head is not equal to null .
Append the value of head to nums array.
Move the head pointer to a position forward.
Now to check whether the given set of array is palindrome or not , we can use 2 pointer technique .
Initialise 2 pointers l and r as 0 and len(nums)-1 respectively.
By using a while loop until l<r . Check whether the value in l pointer is not equal to value in r pointer , then return False.
Otherwise increment l pointer as l+=1 and r decrement pointer as r-=1.
Return true if the while loop ends .
Code
class Solution:

def isPalindrome(self, head: Optional[ListNode]) -> bool:
    nums=[]
    while head:
        nums.append(head.val)
        head=head.next
    
    l,r=0,len(nums)-1
    while l<r:
        if nums[l]!=nums[r]:
            return False
        l+=1
        r-=1
    return True
Complexity
Time complexity:

We use while head: loop which loops through the array and appends the item to an array nums -> O(n)

while l<r: -> This takes O(n)

Overall time complexity : O(n)

Space Complexity:

Use of variables like l , r takes O(1) space complexity

Meanwhile nums[] takes O(n)

Overall : O(n)
